{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"gracefulDisconnect","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A graceful disconnect means that we can be sure that we successfully sent"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"all the outstanding data to the other end, or get an error reported.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However, it also means we have to wait for all the data to reach the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"other side and for it to acknowledge this by closing the socket, which may","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"take a while. For this reason it is disabled by default."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/tcpconnection\/set(gracefuldisconnect:)"]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TcpConnection\/set(gracefulDisconnect:)"},"metadata":{"externalID":"s:3GIO21TcpConnectionProtocolPAAE3set18gracefulDisconnectySb_tF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3GIO13TcpConnectionC","title":"set(gracefulDisconnect:)","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Instance Method","extendedModule":"GIO","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"set"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"gracefulDisconnect","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"role":"symbol"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TcpConnection","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TcpConnection\/TcpConnectionProtocol-Implementations"]]},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This enables graceful disconnects on close. A graceful disconnect"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"means that we signal the receiving end that the connection is terminated"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and wait for it to close the connection before closing the connection.","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/SocketConnection":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SocketConnection","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SocketConnection","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketConnection","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/socketconnection","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSocketConnection"},{"type":"text","text":" is a [class"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOStream","isActive":true},{"text":"] for a connected socket. They","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"can be created either by [class"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketClient","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] when connecting to a host,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"or by [class","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketListener","type":"reference"},{"text":"] when accepting a new client.","type":"text"}],"title":"SocketConnection"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/TcpConnection/set(gracefulDisconnect:)":{"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/tcpconnection\/set(gracefuldisconnect:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This enables graceful disconnects on close. A graceful disconnect"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"means that we signal the receiving end that the connection is terminated"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and wait for it to close the connection before closing the connection.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","title":"set(gracefulDisconnect:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"gracefulDisconnect","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TcpConnection\/set(gracefulDisconnect:)"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/TcpConnection/TcpConnectionProtocol-Implementations":{"title":"TcpConnectionProtocol Implementations","kind":"article","role":"collectionGroup","abstract":[],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/tcpconnection\/tcpconnectionprotocol-implementations","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TcpConnection\/TcpConnectionProtocol-Implementations","type":"topic"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/TcpConnection":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This is the subclass of [class"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketConnection"},{"type":"text","text":"] that is created"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"for TCP\/IP sockets."}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"TcpConnection"}],"title":"TcpConnection","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"TcpConnection","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TcpConnection","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/tcpconnectio